00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:58,480
doomsday bomb inside, protected where 
no one's going to come and stop you.

494
00:37:58,480 --> 00:38:03,200
Yeah, because one of the hardest parts about an 
acorn when you plant it is making sure a squirrel  

495
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:08,760
doesn't dig that fucker up. There's so many things 
that can destroy it, and just keeping it, allowing  

496
00:38:08,760 --> 00:38:14,200
it some space and allowing it some time is the 
most important thing. And it's challenging to do,  

497
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:18,120
but that's why it's important as a leader to 
have enough credibility in the organization  

498
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:23,480
that people can see that you are doing useful 
work to give you the space, to give your team  

499
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:27,840
the space to do this truly great work. If 
you want to get your team to do good work,  

500
00:38:27,840 --> 00:38:31,440
there's a million different paths to do that. 
If you want to get your team to do great work,  

501
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:35,160
there's no shortcut other than to have 
an extremely high-trust environment where  

502
00:38:35,160 --> 00:38:38,880
people lean into their superpowers in 
a way that adds up to something greater  

503
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:42,240
than some of its parts. That takes time. It 
takes effort. It's very difficult to make  

504
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:46,760
legible up to the rest of the organization, 
but that is where great things come from.

505
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:51,800
It reminds me of something Ed Catmull shared in 
