506
00:38:51,800 --> 00:38:56,480
that every new idea is an ugly baby and nobody 
wants this ugly baby. Everyone's just like,  

507
00:38:56,480 --> 00:39:00,240
"Get this out of here," because 
every new idea is bad initially.

508
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:06,560
Yeah, it sucks. They're just like this ugly thing 
that barely works or... But this is why what I try  

509
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:10,560
to do is I try to see the greatness, the seeds of 
greatness in everything. Everyone and everything  

510
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:16,640
around me, I look for, I try to find and see, man, 
what is the most compelling part of this? And let  

511
00:39:16,640 --> 00:39:20,120
me lean into that. And so one of the things I try 
to do when I meet with people, when I mentor them,  

512
00:39:20,120 --> 00:39:24,960
I try with it within the first session or two, 
whenever I can get a hypothesis, I say, "I think  

513
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:31,000
your superpower is..." And I describe to them what 
I think I can see them being truly exceptional at. 

514
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:33,680
And sometimes I get it wrong, 
especially if I try to do it earlier,  

515
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:38,800
but when people feel very seen and they feel 
